.\" wxreversi.6 - manual page for wxReversi
.\" Content derived from the original Windows Reversi help (wxreversichm).
.TH WXREVERSI 6 "April 2026" "wxReversi 1.0" "Games"
.SH NAME
wxreversi \- portable wxWidgets port of the classic Windows Reversi game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxreversi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wxReversi
is a cross-platform port of the Reversi game that shipped with early
versions of Microsoft Windows. You play the red circles; the computer
plays the blue circles. (On monochrome displays, red shows as white and
blue as black.) The object of the game is to finish with more of your
circles on the board than the computer has of its own.
.PP
Playing Reversi involves three things: choosing a skill level, making a
move, and (optionally) asking the computer for a hint. Each of these is
described below.
.SH PLAYING THE GAME
.SS Choosing a Skill Level
Select a skill level from the
.B Skill
menu. The higher the skill level, the longer the computer spends
calculating its moves.
.SS Making a Move
.IP 1. 4
Move the pointer to a free square. The pointer changes to a cross if you
can make a legal move. To make a legal move, at least one of the
computer's circles must lie in a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line
between one of your existing circles and the square where you want to
move.
.IP 2. 4
Click the square where you want to move, or press
.BR Return .
.IP 3. 4
Wait for the computer to move. Then make another move.
.SS Getting a Hint
Choose
.B Hint
from the
.B Game
menu. The hint depends on the skill level selected. At higher skill
levels, the computer takes more time before offering a hint. You can
accept the suggestion or move elsewhere.
.SS Passing Your Turn
Choose
.B Pass
from the
.B Game
menu. You can pass on your first move to force the computer to play
first. After that, you cannot pass if you can make a legal move.
.SS Starting a New Game
Choose
.B New
from the
.B Game
menu.
.SH KEYBOARD
Use the following keys to play Reversi:
.TP
direction keys
Move the pointer.
.TP
.B Return
or
.B Space
Make a move.
.SH GAME MENU
.TP
.B Hint
Suggests a move for you. A cross appears over the square the computer
would choose if it were its turn to play. You can accept the suggestion
or move elsewhere.
.TP
.B Pass
Skips your turn, giving the move to the computer. You can pass on your
first move to force the computer to make the first play. After that, you
may pass only when you cannot make a legal move.
.TP
.B New
Starts a new game. You may start a new game at any time, even before you
finish the current one.
.TP
.B Exit
Exits wxReversi.
.SH SKILL MENU
The
.B Skill
commands set how deeply the computer searches for its moves. The higher
the skill level, the more time the computer spends calculating.
.TP
.B Beginner
The lowest skill level.
.TP
.B Novice
The second lowest skill level.
.TP
.B Expert
The second highest skill level.
.TP
.B Master
The highest skill level.
.SH RULES
.IP 1. 4
You and the computer play by the same rules.
.IP 2. 4
To make a legal move, you must choose a square in which the pointer
changes to a cross.
.IP 3. 4
You can pass on your first move to force the computer to play first.
.IP 4. 4
After your first move, you cannot pass if you can make a legal move.
.IP 5. 4
If you cannot make a legal move, you must choose
.B Pass
from the
.B Game
menu.
.IP 6. 4
When neither you nor the computer can make a move, the game is over.
.IP 7. 4
The player with the most circles wins.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/wxreversi/wxreversi.help
HTML help bundle (same content as this manual page, viewable in a
browser via the Help menu).
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/wxreversi.desktop
Desktop entry for the application menu.
